-- FTSE 100 Drops for First Day in Three, Led by HSBC, BP, Standard Chartered
-- Adam Haigh
-- 2010-07-23T09:31:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/ftse-100-drops-for-first-day-in-three-led-by-hsbc-bp-standard-chartered.html

          
          
             U.K. stocks declined, with the
benchmark FTSE 100 Index falling for the first time in three
days. The gauge lost 0.4 percent to 5,294.66 as of 10:31 a.m. in
London.  
          
          


  


        